  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Qbft voting RPCs should be disabled if we switch to using the validator contract with a transition\r\n\r\n**Acceptance Criteria**\r\n* After switching from a block header voting mode to validator contract mode the QBFT rpcs should return unimplemented error.\r\n* Later if switching back to block header mode the RPCs should work again\r\n* These should also work on initial startup with RPCs only working for block header voting\r\n* Similarly needs to work for toggle on QBFT config validatorContractAddress field\r\n* The qbft_getSignerMetrics should continue to work in both cases as it affected by voting changes",
